If you have any questions,
 you just call me, okay?

03:33.914 --> 03:35.347
- Okay.

03:35.349 --> 03:36.515
- I'm so glad
 you're coming to visit me.

03:36.517 --> 03:37.316
- I'm
  excited to see you.

03:37.318 --> 03:38.250
- I love you.

03:38.252 --> 03:38.784
- I love you too.

03:38.786 --> 03:39.585
Bye.

03:58.205 --> 04:00.272
- More champagne, please.

04:03.110 --> 04:04.042
That's good.

04:04.878 --> 04:06.311
Hi!

04:06.313 --> 04:08.413
Anne from accounting
 brought her brother again.

04:08.415 --> 04:09.915
He was asking about you.

04:09.917 --> 04:11.316
- No, no.

04:11.318 --> 04:14.353
- If you wanna let a perfectly
 good man go to waste,

04:14.355 --> 04:16.855
then I'll take him for you.

04:21.995 --> 04:23.328
- Having fun, Lucy?

04:23.330 --> 04:24.162
- Oh,

04:25.099 --> 04:27.766
Hi, Mr. Feeney, yes I am.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.268
It's a great party.

04:29.270 --> 04:31.403
- You had an amazing year,
 thanks to these people.

04:31.405 --> 04:32.371
And you.

04:32.373 --> 04:34.406
- Thank you, Mr. Feeney.

04:34.408 --> 04:39.378
- Could I speak with you
 for a moment, in private.

04:39.380 --> 04:40.212
- Sure.

04:43.183 --> 04:44.416
Junior partner?

04:44.418 --> 04:45.450
- Why not?

04:45.452 --> 04:46.685
You've certainly earned it.

04:46.687 --> 04:48.487
- I, I don't know what
  to say, Mr. Feeney.

04:48.489 --> 04:51.189
- Well, you can start
  by calling me Joe.

04:51.191 --> 04:52.624
- Thank you, Joe.

04:52.626 --> 04:55.961
- We'll talk later,
  but congratulations.

05:01.201 --> 05:05.037
- Alice, you are not gonna
 believe what just happened!

05:05.039 --> 05:09.708
Uncle Barney, what are you
 doing with Alice's phone?

05:12.346 --> 05:13.178
What?

05:19.420 --> 05:20.252
No, no.

05:28.162 --> 05:30.896
- Don't worry about a
thing here at the office, Lucy.

05:30.898 --> 05:32.431
If there's anything I can do,

05:32.433 --> 05:35.167
please don't hesitate to ask.

05:35.169 --> 05:36.902
- Thank you, Joe.

05:36.904 --> 05:38.904
- Take care, Lucy.

06:08.402 --> 06:10.268
- I'll help you.

06:12.506 --> 06:14.406
- Thanks, Alice.

06:19.113 --> 06:21.046
- What are sisters for?

07:43.163 --> 07:45.063
- Your sister's very good.

07:45.065 --> 07:46.398
Do you play?

07:46.400 --> 07:47.899
- Um, no, I don't.

08:38.251 --> 08:39.083
- Lucy!

08:40.020 --> 08:41.385
Where are you going?

08:41.388 --> 08:42.821
- To Peter's.

08:42.823 --> 08:44.222
I'm gonna help him
  decorate the tree.

08:44.224 --> 08:46.258
- Well we haven't
  had a chance to talk

08:46.260 --> 08:47.692
since I got home from school.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.528
- We can catch up tomorrow.

08:49.530 --> 08:52.297
Relax, we've got lots of time.

08:52.299 --> 08:53.999
- There's something I
 need to tell you, and I'm,

08:54.001 --> 08:57.168
- Alice, can't it
  wait until tomorrow?

08:58.338 --> 08:59.871
Besides, your audience
  wants another song.

09:01.408 --> 09:03.275
- You were great
  in there, Alice.

09:03.277 --> 09:04.442
You played beautiful.

09:04.444 --> 09:05.410
- Thank you, Peter.

09:05.412 --> 09:06.511
- Ready to go?

09:06.513 --> 09:07.712
- Yes.

09:07.714 --> 09:09.347
- Lucy!

09:09.349 --> 09:10.882
It's important.

09:10.884 --> 09:12.751
- All right, fine.

09:12.753 --> 09:14.786
Pick me up from Peter's at 10.

09:14.788 --> 09:16.955
And can talk then, okay?

09:16.957 --> 09:17.956
- Thank you.

09:24.965 --> 09:26.398
- Lucy?

09:26.400 --> 09:27.766
You here?

09:29.770 --> 09:31.870
- I'm here, Uncle Barney.

09:37.244 --> 09:38.243
- Hi, honey.

09:42.149 --> 09:42.981
I'm sorry.

09:45.285 --> 09:46.351
I'm so sorry.

09:49.923 --> 09:51.122
It was sudden.

09:52.225 --> 09:55.160
The doctor said there
  wasn't any pain.

09:56.463 --> 09:58.563
It was one of her heart valves.

09:58.565 --> 10:00.966
They didn't even
  know it was there.

10:00.968 --> 10:02.934
Said it could have
 ruptured at any moment.

10:02.936 --> 10:05.103
- I can't believe
  she's really gone.

10:05.105 --> 10:07.706
I just talked to her last week.

10:09.009 --> 10:10.108
She was fine.

10:11.278 --> 10:13.211
- Hasn't quite hit
  me yet, either.

10:13.213 --> 10:15.580
Seems like we were just
 putting up Christmas lights

10:15.582 --> 10:16.848
the other day.

10:22.155 --> 10:24.489
You know how she loved that.

10:29.196 --> 10:31.429
It's good to see you, Lucy.

10:32.933 --> 10:35.066
How long you planning to stay?

10:35.068 --> 10:37.535
- I have to leave right
 after the funeral.

10:37.537 --> 10:39.170
The day after tomorrow.

10:39.172 --> 10:40.138
- That soon?

10:42.709 --> 10:44.743
- You know, I wish
  I could stay longer.

10:44.745 --> 10:46.678
- We haven't seen you up here,

10:46.680 --> 10:50.448
well, since your folks
 died, 10 or 11 years ago.

10:50.450 --> 10:53.585
- I'm a corporate
  lawyer, Uncle Barney.

10:53.587 --> 10:56.221
You know my time isn't my own.

10:56.223 --> 10:57.155
- I get it.

10:59.860 --> 11:03.495
Time moves pretty
  fast these days.

11:03.497 --> 11:06.197
- Uncle Barney, thank
 you for doing all this.

11:06.199 --> 11:07.098
- Oh, baby.

11:08.969 --> 11:11.936
I haven't done everything.

11:11.938 --> 11:14.839
There's still Alice's estate
 you have to deal with.

11:14.841 --> 11:15.840
- Me?

11:15.842 --> 11:17.142
- Yeah, you're the next of kin.

11:17.144 --> 11:19.644
She probably left
  this place to you.

11:19.646 --> 11:22.080
I guess you've got
 some decisions to make.

12:31.218 --> 12:33.284
- Merry Christmas, Alice.

12:39.459 --> 12:42.360
- The kids were grown,
  and Harold was gone,

12:42.362 --> 12:44.829
and I was just all
  alone in that house.

12:44.831 --> 12:48.032
And then one day there's
 a knock at my door,

12:48.034 --> 12:52.103
and your sister is standing
 there with a kitten.

12:52.105 --> 12:54.773
Alice was always so
  good with animals.

12:54.775 --> 12:57.876
She was studying to be a
 veterinarian before her...

12:59.613 --> 13:00.845
before.

13:00.847 --> 13:02.113
- I am glad she ended up
 at the animal shelter,

13:02.115 --> 13:03.414
because I never I
  never even thought

13:03.416 --> 13:05.884
of having a cat, but
  it was like she knew

13:05.886 --> 13:08.153
what I needed before I did.

13:09.923 --> 13:11.623
I'll betcha half the people
 in this room would tell

13:11.625 --> 13:13.158
you the same thing.

13:13.160 --> 13:16.127
Your sister changed my life.

13:16.129 --> 13:17.962
- Thank you.

13:26.106 --> 13:28.373
I had no idea Alice
  knew so many people.

13:28.375 --> 13:31.576
- Your sister was a very
 big part of this town.

13:31.578 --> 13:33.845
When she started working
 for the animal shelter,

13:33.847 --> 13:35.747
she turned that place around.

13:35.749 --> 13:39.684
- And I don't remember them
 ever letting pets into church.

13:39.686 --> 13:41.186
- That was Alice, too.

13:41.188 --> 13:42.887
She thought it was unfair
 that people had to leave

13:42.889 --> 13:45.857
their pets home alone
  on Sunday mornings,

13:45.859 --> 13:47.492
so she put together a petition,

13:47.494 --> 13:50.495
and she went door to door,
 and got enough signatures

13:50.497 --> 13:52.564
to make City Hall
  change the bylaw.

13:52.566 --> 13:53.431
- She did that?

13:53.433 --> 13:54.265
- {Barney] Um hmm.

13:54.267 --> 13:55.433
- All by herself?

13:55.435 --> 13:57.702
- Well she had a little
 help from the FOA.

13:57.704 --> 13:58.970
- The FOA?

13:58.972 --> 13:59.838
- Lucy?

14:03.610 --> 14:04.609
- Hello, um.

14:10.016 --> 14:10.849
Oh, um.

14:12.419 --> 14:17.856
- Your sister was such a bright
light in all of our lives.

14:22.629 --> 14:24.429
Thank you, um.

14:24.431 --> 14:25.463
- Oh, I'm, I'm sorry.

14:25.465 --> 14:26.664
I'm Daphne.

14:26.666 --> 14:29.200
This is Celia and Rinda.

14:29.202 --> 14:32.704
I imagine that Alice
  told you about us.

14:32.706 --> 14:34.138
- Well, um.

14:34.140 --> 14:37.041
- We're the friends of Alice.

14:37.043 --> 14:38.142
- The FOA.

14:38.144 --> 14:38.977
- Yeah.
   - Yeah.

14:38.979 --> 14:40.511
- Um hmm.

14:40.513 --> 14:42.013
- We just wanted to let you
 know that if need anything,

14:42.015 --> 14:46.317
or if we can do anything,
 you can call us anytime.

14:46.319 --> 14:47.652
Really, anytime.

14:48.521 --> 14:50.822
- Thank you, all of you, um.

14:52.392 --> 14:53.892
It means a lot.

14:53.894 --> 14:56.027
- Your sister, she used
 to call us, day or night,

14:56.029 --> 14:57.996
whenever she needed anything.

14:57.998 --> 15:00.198
We were always there for her.

15:00.200 --> 15:01.766
- Well, like I said, thank you.

15:01.768 --> 15:04.469
I, I really appreciate...

15:19.819 --> 15:23.354
If you would excuse
  me please, um,

15:23.356 --> 15:26.190
I just need to get
  some fresh air.

16:12.806 --> 16:14.238
- Hello.

16:14.240 --> 16:16.641
Oh, hi, Mrs. Toomey.

16:20.180 --> 16:22.146
It's for you, Lucy.

16:22.148 --> 16:24.182
It's about your sister.

16:24.184 --> 16:26.584
- I was
  afraid you'd left.

16:31.591 --> 16:33.091
- Hi.

16:33.093 --> 16:35.860
- Hi.

16:35.862 --> 16:38.529
Lucy, I'm so sorry about Alice.

16:38.531 --> 16:39.964
She was such a wonderful woman,

16:39.966 --> 16:42.900
and I know she
  loved you very much.

16:44.604 --> 16:45.603
- Thank you.

16:47.040 --> 16:48.639
It's good to see you.

16:48.641 --> 16:49.474
- You too.

16:56.216 --> 16:57.882
It's a nice service.

16:59.753 --> 17:00.918
- Yes, it was.

17:02.255 --> 17:05.423
- If you get any time tomorrow,

17:05.425 --> 17:07.992
maybe we could go grab
 some coffee or something.

17:07.993 --> 17:10.627
- I can't, I'm leaving tomorrow.

17:10.630 --> 17:11.863
- Oh, you're not
  gonna stick around

17:11.865 --> 17:13.297
for the tree lighting
  ceremony next week?

17:13.299 --> 17:16.099
You know it was one of
 Alice's favorite events.

17:16.102 --> 17:18.669
- I can't, I'm sorry.

17:18.671 --> 17:21.172
I booked my flight for right
 after the lawyer comes by

17:21.174 --> 17:22.339
with the will.

17:25.645 --> 17:27.310
- Um, well actually,

17:28.615 --> 17:32.383
- It was good
  to see you, Peter.

17:32.385 --> 17:33.718
Goodbye.

17:41.861 --> 17:44.128
We are just waiting for
 the lawyer to show up.

17:44.130 --> 17:45.830
Of course he's late.

17:45.832 --> 17:48.533
I'll be on the 5:30
 flight out of Milwaukee,

17:48.535 --> 17:50.034
and I'll be in the
  office first thing

17:50.036 --> 17:51.869
in the morning, so reschedule
 that lunch with Harrington.

17:53.139 --> 17:54.405
Karen, I will call you
  back from the airport.

17:54.407 --> 17:55.339
Bye.

17:55.341 --> 17:56.074
- I'll see ya tonight.

17:56.076 --> 17:57.341
- Finally!

17:57.343 --> 17:58.676
- I guess you forgot the
 difference between real

17:58.678 --> 18:00.311
time and Nilson Bay time.

18:00.313 --> 18:02.113
- Yeah, well if this
  guy worked at my firm,

18:02.115 --> 18:03.848
he'd be fired in
  a New York minute.

18:07.787 --> 18:09.053
What are you doing here?

18:09.055 --> 18:11.923
- I tried to tell you yesterday.

18:11.925 --> 18:14.759
I'm handling your
  sister's estate.

18:15.628 --> 18:17.295
I'm Alice's lawyer.

18:23.436 --> 18:25.336
- This
  doesn't make sense.

18:25.338 --> 18:28.439
Why would Alice leave this
 place to the animal shelter

18:28.441 --> 18:29.974
instead of her own
  flesh and blood?

18:29.976 --> 18:33.244
- Well, that's not
  exactly what she did.

18:33.246 --> 18:35.012
She merely stipulated
  that Lucy has

18:35.014 --> 18:37.048
to fulfill certain
  requirements in order

18:37.050 --> 18:38.583
to inherit this property.

18:38.585 --> 18:39.717
- Like?

18:39.719 --> 18:41.619
- I have to stay here.

18:41.621 --> 18:43.654
I have to live in this house.

18:43.656 --> 18:44.956
For four weeks?

18:44.958 --> 18:46.224
- Exactly.

18:46.226 --> 18:47.725
Otherwise, ownership
  of the property will

18:47.727 --> 18:51.329
then be transferred to the
 Nilson's Bay Animal Rescue.

18:51.331 --> 18:53.598
- On the bright side, that
 takes you through New Year's.

18:53.600 --> 18:55.800
So you can spend Christmas here.

18:55.802 --> 18:57.034
- No I won't.

18:57.036 --> 18:58.603
- Why not?

18:58.605 --> 19:01.205
- Because I'm not
 staying here, that's why.

19:01.207 --> 19:03.474
There has got to be some
 loophole in this thing.

19:04.310 --> 19:05.209
- I'm afraid not.

19:05.211 --> 19:06.878
I drew it up myself.

19:08.248 --> 19:11.516
And Alice was very specific
 about what she wanted.

19:11.518 --> 19:13.851
- But why would she do this?

19:14.721 --> 19:17.021
She knew I lived in New York.

19:17.023 --> 19:19.056
Why would she want
  me to stay here?

19:19.058 --> 19:20.324
- Well you know Alice.

19:20.326 --> 19:21.659
She must have had her reasons.

19:21.661 --> 19:24.896
- And besides, it's
  only four weeks.

19:24.898 --> 19:29.333
- Peter, I can't just uproot
 my life for an entire month.

19:29.335 --> 19:30.735
I have a job.

19:30.737 --> 19:32.737
I have responsibilities.

19:33.640 --> 19:34.739
- Okay, well,

19:35.909 --> 19:37.608
I can draw up the
  de-transfer for you,

19:37.610 --> 19:39.377
and you can sign over the
 property before you go.

19:39.379 --> 19:40.444
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

19:40.446 --> 19:42.313
Lucy, your
  grandparents built it.

19:42.315 --> 19:44.782
It's been in the
  family for decades.

19:44.784 --> 19:47.885
You sure you just
  wanna give it away?

19:53.760 --> 19:54.992
- A month?

19:54.994 --> 19:57.562
Oh, I didn't realize it
 would take that long.

19:57.564 --> 20:01.032
- I know, this is completely
 out of left field,

20:01.034 --> 20:03.501
but I can handle
  my cases from here.

20:03.503 --> 20:07.071
And I can be available for
 videoconferencing anytime

20:07.073 --> 20:08.306
day or night.

20:08.308 --> 20:10.908
- And what happens after
 this four weeks is up?

20:10.910 --> 20:15.279
- I take ownership of the
house and put it on the market.

20:15.281 --> 20:16.914
- You're going to sell it?

20:16.916 --> 20:18.382
- Absolutely.

20:18.384 --> 20:20.718
Trust me, Joe, I
  have no intention

20:20.720 --> 20:23.421
of moving back to Nilson's Bay.

20:23.423 --> 20:25.223
- Joy to da world.

20:27.460 --> 20:29.193
- Okay, well scan the
 signature pages and send

20:29.195 --> 20:32.363
them on to her, and
  CC me on everything.

20:32.365 --> 20:35.700
Yes, I am not coming
 back until the new year.

20:35.702 --> 20:36.534
- I remember you.

20:41.407 --> 20:44.342
- Lucy, did I lose you?

20:44.344 --> 20:45.876
Lucy?

20:45.878 --> 20:49.313
- Uh, listen, I'll call
 you back later if I think

20:49.315 --> 20:50.781
of anything, okay?

21:00.059 --> 21:02.059
- Which one
  do you wanna try?

21:02.061 --> 21:03.661
- That one.

21:03.663 --> 21:07.198
- Hello, girls, what
  can I getcha today?

21:07.200 --> 21:09.700
- Two gingerbread men, please.

21:10.903 --> 21:14.572
- Oh, 'fraid there's
  only one left.

21:15.441 --> 21:16.974
- We'll take it.

21:16.976 --> 21:17.808
- Okay.

21:22.382 --> 21:24.115
- Merry Christmas.

21:24.117 --> 21:25.850
- Merry Christmas.

21:25.852 --> 21:27.418
- Thank you.

21:27.420 --> 21:29.587
- You can have it.

21:32.525 --> 21:33.991
- Now we both can.

21:44.570 --> 21:46.437
- May I help you?

21:46.439 --> 21:47.772
- What?

21:47.774 --> 21:49.674
Oh, I'm sorry.

21:49.676 --> 21:51.742
Just daydreaming, I guess.

21:54.113 --> 21:56.447
Hi, I met you the other day.

21:57.817 --> 21:59.917
You're one of Alice's friends.

21:59.919 --> 22:00.951
- Rinda.

22:00.953 --> 22:02.787
- Rinda, right.

22:02.789 --> 22:03.621
I'm Lucy.

22:04.691 --> 22:05.523
- I know.

22:11.331 --> 22:13.397
- I can't believe
 McHenry's still puts on

22:13.399 --> 22:15.833
the Taste of Christmas party.

22:15.835 --> 22:18.436
- Every year for the last 75.

22:18.438 --> 22:20.371
- It was always
 Alice's favorite night.

22:20.373 --> 22:22.440
- I'm surprised
  you remember that.

22:24.811 --> 22:27.978
- I just need to
  pick up a few things.

22:29.148 --> 22:32.049
- So you stickin'
  around for a while?

22:32.051 --> 22:36.520
- Yeah, just until after
 Christmas, actually.

22:36.522 --> 22:38.656
- And then
  back to New York?

22:38.658 --> 22:41.325
- Yeah, back to New York.

22:47.400 --> 22:49.333
Oh, it's Alice.

22:49.335 --> 22:51.369
- Yeah, she put out
  a can every Christmas

22:51.371 --> 22:54.705
to raise money for
  the animal shelter.

22:54.707 --> 22:56.874
Guess she never
  mentioned that to you.

22:56.876 --> 22:58.876
Or maybe you didn't ask.

23:01.114 --> 23:03.247
- Oh, she loved her
 animals, that's for sure.

23:04.984 --> 23:07.651
- I was very fond
  of your sister.

23:07.653 --> 23:08.552
We all were

23:09.722 --> 23:12.423
- Well Alice was a
  very special person.

23:12.425 --> 23:15.226
- I hope you appreciated
 having her in your life

23:15.228 --> 23:16.727
as much as we did.

23:19.432 --> 23:21.599
Well I have to get
  my recipes together

23:21.601 --> 23:23.334
for A Taste of Christmas.

23:23.336 --> 23:24.168
Excuse me.

23:31.210 --> 23:34.211
al music)

23:45.224 --> 23:47.224
- Excuse me,
  are you Miss Toomey?

23:47.226 --> 23:48.025
- Uh, yes.

23:50.363 --> 23:51.996
How can I help you girls?

23:51.998 --> 23:55.499
- Mom said to bring
  back Miss Alice's cat.

23:56.669 --> 24:00.237
- Well, I'm not staying.

24:00.239 --> 24:02.940
Merry Christmas.

24:08.381 --> 24:10.881
- Great, and now I have a cat.

24:15.755 --> 24:17.688
Okay, okay, I hear you.

24:20.660 --> 24:22.660
All right, okay, I know.

24:25.865 --> 24:26.697
Um, yeah.

24:29.902 --> 24:30.734
All right.

24:32.438 --> 24:33.904
Okay.

24:33.906 --> 24:36.740
Well, come on out, and let's
 get to know each other.

24:39.245 --> 24:42.012
Well it was nice
  to meet you too.

24:43.850 --> 24:44.682
Hello.

24:46.118 --> 24:46.951
Cat.

24:48.721 --> 24:49.553
Kitty.

24:52.091 --> 24:52.923
Kitty.

24:54.494 --> 24:55.359
Cat.

24:56.262 --> 24:57.094
Come on.

25:08.774 --> 25:09.607
- Hi.

25:10.443 --> 25:11.809
- Hi.

25:11.811 --> 25:13.944
- I, uh, got this for Alice.

25:13.946 --> 25:17.581
It was kind of a
  tradition with us.

25:17.583 --> 25:20.951
And I already have mine, so I
 thought maybe you'd like it.

25:20.953 --> 25:24.989
- Um, actually I wasn't
 planning on putting up a tree.

25:24.991 --> 25:27.157
- You do know that in Nilson's
 Bay it's a misdemeanor

25:27.159 --> 25:28.392
not to have a tree?

25:28.394 --> 25:30.194
I mean, you should see
  my office.

25:30.196 --> 25:32.830
I'm just tryin' to keep
 you out of trouble.

25:32.832 --> 25:33.864
Please don't make me
  take it all the way

25:33.866 --> 25:35.566
back home again, please.

25:35.568 --> 25:36.400
- Okay.

25:36.402 --> 25:37.501
- Okay, good.

25:39.839 --> 25:41.105
Okay, look out.

25:42.909 --> 25:43.741
Careful, careful!

25:43.743 --> 25:44.842
- All right, okay!

25:44.844 --> 25:45.976
- Watch yourself.
  - Okay.

25:45.978 --> 25:47.077
- Here we go.

25:52.518 --> 25:53.951
- It's a beautiful tree.

25:53.953 --> 25:56.520
- It has to be.

25:56.522 --> 26:00.424
Alice was very specific
 about her Christmas trees.

26:00.426 --> 26:02.693
- You guys really kept
 in touch all these years?

26:02.695 --> 26:06.030
- Sure, Alice was a
  really great friend.

26:06.933 --> 26:09.867
And in a way,

26:09.869 --> 26:11.168
she kind of, you know,

26:11.170 --> 26:12.002
kept me in touch with

26:12.004 --> 26:13.070
- Hey!

26:13.072 --> 26:14.038
- Oh, wait a second!
  - Okay.

26:14.040 --> 26:15.139
- Ah, I got it.

26:15.141 --> 26:15.973
- Okay.

26:17.410 --> 26:20.578
- I was sayin' that, in
 a way, it kind of kept me

26:20.580 --> 26:22.079
in touch with you too.

26:22.081 --> 26:23.314
- Me?

26:23.316 --> 26:25.583
- She talked about
  you a lot.

26:25.585 --> 26:29.153
And she told me about
  your life, your work,

26:29.155 --> 26:31.188
when you got your hair cut,
 what you had for lunch.

26:31.190 --> 26:33.924
- Sorry.

26:33.926 --> 26:35.125
- Hey, will you
  hold this for a sec?

26:35.127 --> 26:35.960
You got it?

26:35.962 --> 26:37.227
- Uh hmm.

26:37.229 --> 26:38.729
- I'll just
  take this stuff off.

26:39.966 --> 26:42.166
You know, she was my
  very first client.

26:42.168 --> 26:43.567
- Really?

26:43.569 --> 26:46.904
- Yeah, she paid me
  $100 and a goldfish.

26:51.310 --> 26:52.543
All right.

26:52.545 --> 26:53.711
I'm gonna pick this
  up, slide it in there.

26:53.713 --> 26:54.945
- Okay.

26:54.947 --> 26:57.381
- Just make sure
  it goes in there.

26:58.284 --> 26:59.383
- Got it.

26:59.385 --> 27:00.651
- Okay.

27:00.653 --> 27:04.188
Good, funny how we both
 became lawyers, huh?

27:04.190 --> 27:05.356
- Yeah, funny.

27:07.660 --> 27:09.226
Why did you do it?

27:09.228 --> 27:11.862
- Guess I always just wanted
 to fight for the little guy,

27:11.864 --> 27:14.431
you know, make sure
  justice was served.

27:14.433 --> 27:15.366
You?

27:15.368 --> 27:18.302
- Yeah, not exactly the same.

27:18.304 --> 27:22.006
I write contracts to help
 big property development

27:22.008 --> 27:25.142
companies acquire real
 estate and get even bigger.

27:25.144 --> 27:26.310
- You like it?

27:27.279 --> 27:28.312
- I'm good at it.

27:28.314 --> 27:29.313
- Objection.

27:31.684 --> 27:34.284
That's not really what I asked.

27:35.321 --> 27:36.920
- Sometimes I do.

27:36.922 --> 27:38.455
- And the other times?

27:38.457 --> 27:43.193
- I don't know anyone who's
 100% happy at their job.

27:44.664 --> 27:45.496
- I am.

27:51.303 --> 27:53.504
And that looks pretty good.

27:54.607 --> 27:56.807
- Do you know
  anything about cats?

27:56.809 --> 27:58.809
- I see you met Mr. Freckles.

27:58.811 --> 27:59.810
- Mr. Freckles.

27:59.812 --> 28:01.278
- That's his name.

28:01.280 --> 28:03.013
Daphne told me she was
 bringing him back to you.

28:03.015 --> 28:05.082
- Well I wish she had told him.

28:05.084 --> 28:07.184
He took off like a
 shot as soon as we came

28:07.186 --> 28:08.419
through the door.

28:08.421 --> 28:11.689
- I think I know
  where to find him.

28:11.691 --> 28:12.756
Meow!

28:17.430 --> 28:18.262
And voila.

28:28.407 --> 28:30.074
- Oh, there you are.

28:31.544 --> 28:33.510
- He always goes under here
 whenever there's a stranger

28:33.512 --> 28:34.878
in the house.

28:34.880 --> 28:36.413
- I'm not a stranger.

28:36.415 --> 28:37.815
I'm his Aunt Lucy.

28:37.817 --> 28:40.884
- Yeah, but he
  doesn't know that yet.

28:43.556 --> 28:45.289
- Mr. Freckles, here!

28:46.492 --> 28:50.928
I've got some delicious
 creamed liver surprise.

28:50.930 --> 28:51.862
Oh.

28:54.133 --> 28:54.965
Mow.

28:56.035 --> 28:57.468
- No, it's meorw.

28:59.505 --> 29:00.337
- Mow.

29:01.340 --> 29:02.740
- Work on it.

29:02.742 --> 29:05.776
- I can't believe I'm
 being rejected by a cat.

29:05.778 --> 29:10.214
- Ah, it may him awhile,
 but he'll come around.

29:10.216 --> 29:14.551
Remember, we're not the
 only ones who lost somebody.

29:16.021 --> 29:16.854
Ah, hey.

29:22.061 --> 29:24.128
Ah, they didn't finish it.

29:24.130 --> 29:25.062
- They?

29:25.064 --> 29:27.297
- Yeah, the friends of Alice.

29:27.299 --> 29:30.634
They were also sort of a
 quilting bee with your sister.

29:30.636 --> 29:33.237
- Um, do you know who Maeve is?

29:35.174 --> 29:36.240
- Hmm?

29:36.242 --> 29:37.908
- Here, "For Maeve."

29:38.944 --> 29:40.377
Who is that?

29:40.379 --> 29:41.879
- Ah, I can't say.

29:43.382 --> 29:45.215
- It must have been
 someone special to her.

29:45.217 --> 29:46.884
- Yeah, I'm sure they were,

29:46.886 --> 29:50.387
so, do want some help
  decorating the tree?

29:52.892 --> 29:53.857
- Right now?

29:53.859 --> 29:55.225
- Why not?

29:55.227 --> 29:56.894
Christmas is coming.

30:07.439 --> 30:10.107
- Peter, I found these upstairs.

30:11.277 --> 30:13.443
I can't believe she kept
 them all these years.

30:14.280 --> 30:15.379
- Excellent.

30:15.381 --> 30:16.847
And I found some music to put us

30:16.849 --> 30:18.949
in the tree decorating mood.
 ♪ Chestnuts roasting

30:18.951 --> 30:21.118
♪ On an open fire

30:21.120 --> 30:24.021
- Oh, that was my
 parents' favorite album.

30:24.023 --> 30:26.957
- Did you know it
  was Alice's, too?

30:28.761 --> 30:30.727
- I know Peter.

30:30.729 --> 30:32.529
♪ Yule-tide carols

30:32.531 --> 30:35.899
I know that was her
  favorite.

30:35.901 --> 30:37.634
- Oh, hey, I'm sorry.

30:38.971 --> 30:40.270
I didn't mean anything.

30:40.272 --> 30:42.973
It's just, you've
  been gone a while.

30:45.744 --> 30:47.277
- Alice understood.

30:48.747 --> 30:50.380
- I'm sure she did.

30:50.382 --> 30:53.150
- I helped her out a lot, okay,

30:53.152 --> 30:54.818
anything she needed.

30:55.888 --> 30:57.821
And when our
  parents passed away,

30:57.823 --> 31:00.791
I offered to bring
  her to the city,

31:00.793 --> 31:02.759
but she didn't wanna leave.

31:02.761 --> 31:04.628
- Why would she?

31:04.630 --> 31:06.763
This was her home,

31:06.765 --> 31:08.699
yours too, until she...

31:10.236 --> 31:15.105
It was an
  accident, Lucy.

31:15.107 --> 31:17.674
You know that, right?

31:17.676 --> 31:18.976
- Of course I do.

31:18.978 --> 31:21.378
- So what happened?

31:21.380 --> 31:24.314
We were so close, but you
 barely spoke to me after that.

31:24.316 --> 31:27.017
- I barely spoke to a
 lot of people after that.

31:27.019 --> 31:29.353
- Yeah, but you avoided
 me the entire last year

31:29.355 --> 31:30.687
of high school.

31:30.689 --> 31:32.589
And that was some trick,
 considering there were

31:32.591 --> 31:35.859
only 47 people in
  our graduating class.

31:35.861 --> 31:37.895
♪ To you

31:40.532 --> 31:42.499
- The record's over.

31:51.810 --> 31:56.013
- Um, I just remembered,
 I gotta catch up

31:56.015 --> 31:58.849
on some work at the office.

31:58.851 --> 32:00.183
- Oh, okay.

32:00.185 --> 32:01.852
- Yeah, I better go.

32:14.566 --> 32:16.400
- Thanks for the tree.

32:19.471 --> 32:23.774
- You gonna be okay with
 all those decorations?

32:23.776 --> 32:25.008
- Well if I have any trouble,

32:25.010 --> 32:28.578
I could just ask Mr.
  Freckles for help.

32:34.753 --> 32:35.752
- Goodnight.

32:37.456 --> 32:38.455
- Goodnight.

33:17.796 --> 33:19.563
- This one's for you.

33:25.637 --> 33:27.437
- It's so pretty.

33:27.439 --> 33:28.872
Thank you, Alice.

33:50.796 --> 33:52.996
- Your sister was
  a wonderful lady.

33:52.998 --> 33:55.399
You know, she's the reason
 why I got my first dog.

33:55.401 --> 33:56.566
- Really?

33:56.568 --> 33:58.035
- I met her at
  McHenry's one year,

33:58.037 --> 33:59.536
at the Taste of Christmas,
 and before I knew it,

33:59.538 --> 34:01.671
she'd talked me into
  a dachshund.

34:01.673 --> 34:02.873
Best thing that's
  ever happened to me.

34:02.875 --> 34:04.074
I got three of em now.

34:04.076 --> 34:05.542
- Oh.

34:05.544 --> 34:07.744
- So you told me on the
 phone that you were looking

34:07.746 --> 34:09.980
to sell Alice's house.

34:09.982 --> 34:12.516
- Yes, yes, Mr. Glaser,

34:12.518 --> 34:14.351
- Oh, please, Ed.

34:14.353 --> 34:15.918
May I call you Lucy?

34:15.920 --> 34:16.853
- Sure, Ed.

34:18.623 --> 34:20.190
My Uncle Barney recommended you

34:20.192 --> 34:22.726
as the best real
  estate agent in town.

34:22.728 --> 34:24.527
- Well, I'd certainly
  like to think so.

34:24.530 --> 34:26.696
And Nilson's Bay is
  a seller's market.

34:26.697 --> 34:28.465
We have several developers
 that are very interested

34:28.467 --> 34:30.667
in the area, and you
 have enough acreage there

34:30.668 --> 34:34.737
to put at least three
 decent sized pre-fab homes,

34:34.739 --> 34:36.473
maybe even a condo building.

34:36.475 --> 34:37.373
- Wait, um.

34:38.744 --> 34:41.878
You're saying they'd
 wanna tear down our house?

34:41.880 --> 34:44.947
- Well, Miss Toomey,
 it's lakefront property.

34:44.949 --> 34:48.485
One of the last parcels
 to be developed.

34:48.487 --> 34:50.420
- I hadn't really
  thought about that.

34:50.422 --> 34:52.922
- I understand,
  it's a cute house.

34:52.925 --> 34:54.157
But the comps in that area are

34:54.159 --> 34:55.859
in the half a
  million dollar range,

34:55.860 --> 34:57.194
and I'm certain we could
 get you at least that,

34:57.196 --> 34:59.429
maybe even a bit more.

34:59.431 --> 35:00.697
- I don't know.

35:00.699 --> 35:02.199
I'm not sure how I
  feel about having

35:02.201 --> 35:04.201
my family home torn down.

35:04.203 --> 35:06.269
- It's just a
  house, Miss Toomey.

35:06.271 --> 35:08.472
You could always buy
  another one.

35:08.474 --> 35:12.075
At these prices, you
 could probably buy two.

35:12.077 --> 35:15.479
- Well, uh, I have
  to think about it.

35:15.481 --> 35:17.581
Uh, thank you for your time, Ed.

35:17.583 --> 35:19.416
- I'd advise you not
  to think too long.

35:19.418 --> 35:21.485
It's like I always say, when
 opportunity comes callin,

35:21.487 --> 35:23.920
you better answer
  on the first knock.

36:01.693 --> 36:03.960
- Look at
  the tree, girls!

36:03.962 --> 36:06.329
- I like
  when it sparkles.

36:06.331 --> 36:07.597
- Yeah, me too.

36:08.967 --> 36:10.667
- Daphne, right?

36:10.669 --> 36:11.868
- Oh, hi!

36:11.870 --> 36:13.770
Yes, and these are my girls.

36:13.772 --> 36:16.072
This is Ophelia, and Portia.

36:16.074 --> 36:17.908
- The cat delivery service,

36:17.910 --> 36:18.942
right?
  - Yes.

36:18.944 --> 36:19.776
- Hi.

36:19.778 --> 36:21.244
- Hi, Miss Toomey.

36:21.246 --> 36:22.445
- Hi, Miss Toomey.

36:22.447 --> 36:24.181
- How are things goin
  with Mr. Freckles?

36:24.183 --> 36:26.917
- Actually, I don't think
 he likes me.

36:26.919 --> 36:28.585
- Oh, well he will.

36:28.587 --> 36:30.887
It just takes time.

36:30.889 --> 36:34.524
- Daphne, did you ever hear
 her mention the name Maeve?

36:34.526 --> 36:38.361
- Maeve, uh, no, not
 that I can remember, why?

36:39.565 --> 36:41.631
- I found a name tag
  on some quilt pieces

36:41.633 --> 36:42.899
she was working on.

36:42.901 --> 36:44.367
- Well I can tell you
  who those belong to.

36:44.369 --> 36:45.502
They're ours.

36:45.504 --> 36:46.670
- Yours?

36:46.672 --> 36:48.872
- Yeah, Alice, Celia,
  Rinda, and mine.

36:48.874 --> 36:51.608
We were making our annual
 Christmas friendship quilt,

36:51.610 --> 36:54.044
and we'd get together
 once a week to work on it.

36:54.046 --> 36:56.713
- You're welcome to come
 by and get it if you want.

36:56.715 --> 36:58.381
- The thing about a
  friendship quilt is

36:58.383 --> 37:00.383
you have to finish
  it in the same home

37:00.385 --> 37:01.418
that you started it in.

37:01.420 --> 37:04.221
It's kind of a tradition.

37:04.223 --> 37:05.555
- Oh.

37:05.557 --> 37:07.157
- Well, you don't
  mind if we finish

37:07.159 --> 37:09.125
it in your house, do you?

37:09.127 --> 37:10.393
- Oh.

37:10.395 --> 37:11.661
- It won't take long,
  maybe a couple hours,

37:11.663 --> 37:13.830
and we won't make
  a mess, I promise.

37:13.832 --> 37:15.966
- I actually have a
  lot of work to do.

37:15.968 --> 37:19.169
- So Thursday in the
 afternoon, say, five-ish?

37:19.171 --> 37:20.070
I'll bring the cookies.

37:20.072 --> 37:20.904
- This Thursday?

37:20.906 --> 37:21.905
- Okay, great.

37:21.907 --> 37:22.739
Well, we'll see you then.

37:22.741 --> 37:23.673
- Bye.
