37:36.054 --> 37:37.721
- Uh, huh.

37:37.723 --> 37:39.422
Yeah, right.

37:39.424 --> 37:42.892
Well, that would be unfortunate.

37:42.894 --> 37:44.761
I will tell him.

37:44.763 --> 37:45.595
Bye, bye.

37:46.698 --> 37:49.599
Lucy, hi, you're still in town.

37:49.601 --> 37:51.468
- Still here.

37:51.470 --> 37:53.870
I'm looking for Peter Swinson.

37:53.872 --> 37:57.307
- I take it you don't know Mr.
 Swinson real well.

37:57.309 --> 37:58.241
- Why do you say that?

37:58.243 --> 37:59.943
It's 12:30 on a Wednesday.

37:59.945 --> 38:02.812
There's really only one
 place you're gonna find him.

38:18.230 --> 38:19.162
- Hi.

38:20.098 --> 38:21.064
- What are you doin' here?

38:21.066 --> 38:23.066
- I, I need some advice.

38:24.469 --> 38:26.936
- Personal or professional?

38:26.938 --> 38:29.472
- A bit of both, I guess.

38:29.474 --> 38:32.809
- Okay, but it'll
  have to be on the ice.

38:32.811 --> 38:33.910
- What?

38:33.912 --> 38:35.445
- I'm in the middle of class.

38:35.447 --> 38:37.013
- Come on, Mr. Swinson!

38:37.015 --> 38:38.848
- Give me a second!

38:38.850 --> 38:39.683
Well?

38:41.620 --> 38:42.952
Whatta you say?

38:42.954 --> 38:46.156
- It's been a long time
 since I was on skates.

38:46.158 --> 38:48.758
- They say you never
  forget how to do it.

38:48.760 --> 38:51.261
It's like riding a bike.

38:51.263 --> 38:53.630
- It's been a long time
 since I rode a bike, too.

38:53.632 --> 38:55.565
- I won't let you fall.

38:58.470 --> 39:00.170
- Sounds like Ed can
  get you a lot of money

39:00.172 --> 39:01.905
of the property, but...

39:01.907 --> 39:03.340
- But?

39:03.342 --> 39:05.809
- Well I mean, the Toomeys
 have had that house

39:05.811 --> 39:07.544
since before I was born.

39:07.546 --> 39:10.613
You sure you're ready
  to say goodbye to it?

39:10.615 --> 39:13.183
- I guess I'll have to be.

39:13.185 --> 39:15.485
You can't hold on to the past.

39:15.487 --> 39:18.788
- Whoa, comin
  through, Mr. Swinson.

39:18.790 --> 39:20.623
- How long have you
  been doing this?

39:20.625 --> 39:22.225
- Oh, couple years.

39:23.395 --> 39:25.295
Alice was a volunteer
 at the community center,

39:25.297 --> 39:28.498
and she drafted me to teach
 the kids how to skate.

39:28.500 --> 39:29.866
- I'm starting to think
 there wasn't anything

39:29.868 --> 39:31.801
in this town she
  wasn't involved in.

39:31.803 --> 39:33.670
- Yeah, she
 definitely made a difference

39:33.672 --> 39:35.004
in Nilson's Bay.

39:36.975 --> 39:38.608
- Do you think that's why
 she wanted me to be here

39:38.610 --> 39:40.243
for the month?

39:40.245 --> 39:41.745
- What do you mean?

39:41.747 --> 39:45.482
- Maybe she wanted me to
 see how important she was?

39:45.484 --> 39:50.220
- Or maybe she wanted you
 to slow down for a minute.

39:50.222 --> 39:51.921
Stop running from things.

39:51.923 --> 39:54.090
- I'm not running from anything.

39:54.092 --> 39:55.558
- Sure you are.

39:55.560 --> 40:00.163
You ran away from this town,
 away from these people,

40:00.165 --> 40:01.231
away from us.

40:02.934 --> 40:04.534
- Woo, Mr. Swinson.

40:06.171 --> 40:07.237
- All right, that's it.

40:07.239 --> 40:09.239
Guys, that's it for today.

40:09.241 --> 40:10.673
Everybody off the ice.

40:10.675 --> 40:11.808
Hot cocoa's on me.

40:11.810 --> 40:13.977
- Yes!

40:17.182 --> 40:19.482
- I'm not running
  from anything, Peter.

40:19.484 --> 40:23.186
I just don't wanna
  live in the past.

40:23.188 --> 40:26.089
- You may not be living
 in the past, Lucy,

40:26.091 --> 40:29.959
but I think the past is
 still kinda living in you.

40:42.774 --> 40:43.807
- I've arranged
  for an extension

40:43.809 --> 40:45.074
on the Harrington case.

40:45.076 --> 40:47.811
- Joe, you didn't
  have to do that.

40:47.813 --> 40:50.513
I've been keeping up with
 things from this end, and,

40:50.515 --> 40:53.283
- I understand, but the client
 needs a face-to-face meeting

40:53.285 --> 40:56.052
before he'll proceed,
 so you're due back here,

40:56.054 --> 40:58.388
on, what is it now, three weeks?

40:58.390 --> 40:59.823
- Uh, huh.

40:59.825 --> 41:01.124
- You know, we could
 challenge your sister's

41:01.126 --> 41:02.625
will in court.

41:02.627 --> 41:04.494
I still don't understand
 why she needed you to stay

41:04.496 --> 41:06.229
in the house this long.

41:06.231 --> 41:07.997
- Uh, I'm not sure either.

41:11.903 --> 41:13.136
Wow.

41:13.138 --> 41:15.271
Uh, I'm going to have
  to call you back.

41:15.273 --> 41:16.940
I'll call you later.

41:18.343 --> 41:19.175
- Goodbye.

41:21.980 --> 41:23.313
- There you are.

41:25.450 --> 41:27.283
So now you wanna play?

41:34.359 --> 41:35.325
I guess not.

41:51.910 --> 41:53.743
What are these, Alice?

41:56.348 --> 41:57.614
Self portraits?

42:13.164 --> 42:16.165
- Hi, I brought
  the cookies, whoo.

42:16.167 --> 42:17.667
- I didn't think we were
 gonna make it up that hill.

42:17.669 --> 42:19.135
- I mean, Rinda, if you
 would just put the chains

42:19.137 --> 42:20.303
on those tires.

42:20.305 --> 42:21.538
- My tires are perfectly fine.

42:21.540 --> 42:22.472
- Oooh.

42:22.474 --> 42:23.406
- It's the ice on the roads.

42:23.408 --> 42:24.807
They don't use enough salt.

42:24.809 --> 42:26.042
- They can't use that much salt.

42:26.044 --> 42:27.377
It's bad for the deer.

42:27.379 --> 42:28.711
- Oh, so because of the deer,

42:28.713 --> 42:29.812
you have to drive off the road.

42:29.814 --> 42:31.748
- That's why you
  need the chains.

42:31.750 --> 42:32.916
- I like deer.

