He runs away every
  time I try to pet him.

45:39.504 --> 45:41.838
- Don't worry.

45:41.840 --> 45:43.439
He'll warm up to you.

45:43.441 --> 45:44.507
It's just like I
  said the other day.

45:44.509 --> 45:46.542
It's gonna take time.

45:49.748 --> 45:51.681
I think he still misses Alice.

45:51.683 --> 45:54.350
- What was she like, Lucy?

45:54.352 --> 45:56.385
We all knew her
  after the accident.

45:56.387 --> 46:00.123
It's just, she never, she
 never talked about that day.

46:00.125 --> 46:01.791
- Um, she was funny.

46:06.264 --> 46:10.767
And kind, I mean she'd just
 about do anything for you.

46:12.504 --> 46:14.504
- I guess in a lot of
 ways that really matter

46:14.506 --> 46:15.905
she was the same.

46:17.175 --> 46:21.177
- Maybe, but before the
 accident, everything was

46:26.384 --> 46:28.384
so effortless for Alice.

46:29.554 --> 46:33.089
I think that was
  the hardest part,

46:33.091 --> 46:35.892
watching her
  struggle with things

46:35.894 --> 46:37.627
like buttoning a shirt,

46:37.629 --> 46:41.631
or playing her violin.

46:44.569 --> 46:46.936
I, I, I think I'm
  done for tonight.

46:46.938 --> 46:50.706
- Yeah, yeah we can, we'll
 pick this up another day.

46:50.708 --> 46:52.708
- Oh, it's okay, I'm not tired.

46:52.710 --> 46:53.943
- Oh.

46:53.945 --> 46:57.213
- Oh, wow, yeah,
  look at the time.

46:57.215 --> 46:58.047
- You should go.
  - You should go.

47:00.919 --> 47:02.552
- Will you call us
  if you need anything?

47:02.554 --> 47:04.453
- Thanks for having us.

47:06.024 --> 47:07.290
Pretty soon we're gonna
 have to make a quilt

47:07.292 --> 47:09.692
for the baby, yeah.

47:11.963 --> 47:12.795
Thank you.

47:14.632 --> 47:15.898
- Oh, don't forget
  to hide those squares

47:15.900 --> 47:17.099
from Mr. Freckles.

